            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and the<strong> harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>harissa stock</strong></p><p>Once the courgette has softened, add the <strong>harissa stock</strong> and <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until the sauce has thickened to a bolognese-like consistency – this is your <strong>harissa meat-free mince ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
